Luckie Base Rails 3 Application Template

NOTE: This template requires Ruby 1.9 and Rails 3

If you don't already have Rails 3 running:

  rvm update
  rvm reload
  rvm install 1.9.2 -C --enable-shared=yes
  rvm use ruby-1.9.2-p0
  gem install rails

To create a new Rails 3 app based on the Luckie Template:

  rails new my_app --database=mysql --template=~/projects/jumpstart/luckie_template.rb
